abstract: When 10 New York jockeys were implicated last week in a race-fixing scheme, it came with all the surprise of an odds-on favorite winning by a dozen lengths. For years, there was knowledge of an investigation; for months, the names of star jockeys were bruited about; for days, indictments had been expected.
headline_main: The Future Of Racing In New York Is in Dispute; Growing Consensus on a Takeover

abstract: "I was shaving the other morning," a former racing official said, "when I heard a television commercial left over from last winter: 'C'mon out to Aqueduct,' it said, 'it's the hottest place in town.'"

abstract: A California restaurateur testified yesterday that Con Errico, the former jockey, was in Los Angeles at a time when the Government contends he conspired to fix a race at Aqueduct.

abstract: The Government completed its case yesterday against Con Errico, the 58year-old former jockey who has been accused of conspiring to fix nine thoroughbred horse races at Aqueduct and Saratoga in 1974 and 1975.
